// Root cause: in RTL read logic:
//   BUGGY:  rd_ptr <= rd_ptr + 1;  // increments first!
//           rd_data <= mem[rd_ptr]; // reads from WRONG address
//
//   FIXED:  rd_data <= mem[rd_ptr]; // read first
//           rd_ptr  <= rd_ptr + 1;  // then increment

// Key insight: the scoreboard reported wrong output at t=1250ns
// but the bug happened at t=1240ns (wrong pointer increment order)
